    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A top-down narrative SPA structure was chosen to guide recruiters logically through the candidate's professional story. It starts with a strong value proposition (Hero), provides a detailed summary (About), showcases tangible proof of skills through interactive project case studies with charts (Projects), offers a filterable overview of technical capabilities (Skills), and finishes with career history and contact details. This structure prioritizes impact and proof over simple chronology, which is more effective for demonstrating value quickly. Key interactions like project tabbing and skill filtering are designed to make dense information easily digestible and engaging. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Project impact (Hours Saved). Goal: Compare. Viz: Bar Chart (Chart.js). Interaction: Toggling between projects updates the chart to show before/after efficiency gains. Justification: Visually proves the value of automation skills.
        - Report Info: Extensive list of computer skills. Goal: Organize & Compare. Viz: Horizontal Bar Chart (Chart.js). Interaction: Category filter buttons update the chart. Justification: Prevents overwhelming the user with a long list and allows them to focus on relevant skill sets.
        - Report Info: Career achievements. Goal: Inform & Impress. Viz: HTML/CSS Icon Cards. Interaction: Subtle hover effects. Justification: Breaks up text and highlights key accomplishments in a scannable format.
        - Report Info: General resume data. Goal: Inform. Viz: Styled HTML text blocks. Justification: Standard, clear presentation for background information.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
